Maybe you've heard of the "missing tile" effect -- when we walk into a room, and only notice the missing tile on the ceiling, without thinking much about the EXISTING tiles. Everyday, life throws at us a mix of positive and negative, but rather than paying attention to the positive, we dwell on the "missing tiles". Think of all the good stuff that we're missing! >>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>> I found that taking 5-10 minutes everyday to reflect on the above points has really helped me correct this distortion. Keeping a note file on my phone or Google doc is the easiest 👌
